# ─── Dependencies ───
node_modules/

# ─── Build output (compiled JS bundle, regenerated on every build) ───
bin/

# ─── DCL runtime auto-generated artifacts ───
# CRDT state files written by `sdk-commands start` — regenerate on next preview.
# If checked in stale they can break "edit-mode" composite editing.
main.crdt
main1.crdt

# ─── Environment / secrets ───
# .env files may hold Auth Server EnvVars (API keys, private keys for signed
# requests, etc.). Never commit them — secrets belong in env vars only.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ─── Creator Hub workspace state (local, per-user) ───
.editor/

# ─── Logs ───
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# ─── OS noise ───
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ─── IDE — keep shared config, ignore personal ───
# .vscode/extensions.json + launch.json ARE versioned (shared with the team).
# .vscode/settings.json is per-user (user-specific keybinds, formatters, etc).
.vscode/settings.json
.vscode/*.code-workspace
.idea/

# ─── Claude Code — local settings only ───
# Keep .claude/skills/ versioned so anyone cloning gets the SDK skills setup.
# Keep CLAUDE.md and GAME_DESIGN.md versioned (in repo root).
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/sessions/

# Memory dir lives in C:\Users\Santi\.claude\projects\... outside the repo,
# so it's already not tracked. No rule needed here.

# ─── Notes on what is INTENTIONALLY versioned ───
# - package-lock.json   (reproducible builds, npm best practice)
# - assets/Models/      (downloaded GLBs are part of the scene)
# - assets/Audio/       (downloaded MP3s are part of the scene)
# - assets/scene/main.composite, entity-names.ts
# - assets/asset-packs/ (Creator Hub asset packs the team uses)
# - assets/images/      (thumbnails referenced by scene.json)
# - dclcontext/         (project-shared SDK reference docs)
# - thumbnails/         (auto-generated scene thumbnails — small, useful)
# - skills-lock.json    (lock file for `npx skills add`)
# - .cursor/, cursor.config, cursorignore  (shared Cursor config)
